+## Attempt 16 Review Response
+
+<!-- REVIEW: added per attempt-16-global-synthesis -->
+
+Attempt 16 still blocks behavior-moving decomposition. This revision keeps
+`design_review.verdict=iterate`: non-mutating Slice 0 evidence gathering may
+continue, but no mutation, routing, worker-boundary, event, runtime, or public
+wire behavior may move until the required rows, validators, and proof commands
+exist and pass.
+
+| Finding | Active design response |
+|---|---|
+| Slice 0 parity proof can pass without proving current behavior. | Make `SLICE0_CONTRACT.yaml` the close gate for Slice 0. It must enumerate every validator and proof command, fail on missing validators, skipped tests, build-tag exclusions, zero matched selectors, stale paths, absent negative fixtures, or any active `SESSION-*` row without current executed proof or owner-approved amendment/retirement. `SCENARIO_PARITY.yaml` must map each active row to exact slices, surfaces, routes, current oracle, characterization proof, and proof command. |
+| Atomic mutation semantics lack a real store and fence contract. | Add `STORE_CAPABILITY_MATRIX.yaml` before any mutating slice. Each operation row must choose exactly one fence strategy: store-native conditional write; durable value/token/revision precondition with immediate reread; or explicitly repair-converged blind write with eligibility limits, supersession keys, post-write verification, and failure-injection tests. Unknown store capability blocks mutation. |
+| Migration and worker-boundary sequencing are not source-complete. | Replace file-name triggers with inventory-driven rows from `SESSION_BOUNDARY_SYMBOLS.yaml`, `API_CLI_ROUTE_INVENTORY.yaml`, and `WORKER_BOUNDARY_EXCEPTIONS.yaml`. Every API/CLI mutating lifecycle path either routes through `worker.Handle` or has an exact expiring exception with route, symbol, key family, parity, rollback, and retirement proof. |
+| Read-only target classification can fork materializing resolver behavior. | Add a shared-resolver sequencing rule: read-only and materializing modes must share one precedence source until materialization migrates, or anti-drift tests must compare match vectors and result kinds for both modes. `repair-needed` must be endpoint-specific, with repair scheduler, retry or degraded-result behavior, current successful lookup preservation, persistence-error propagation, and repair fence. |
+| Target-classification output risks becoming a flat optional facade. | Treat the current field list as a provisional field census. The first adopter may only expose fields it consumes; non-first-adopter fields are forbidden in active Go structs, OpenAPI/generated-client types, event payloads, and cross-slice contracts until a checkpoint row promotes them. Production results must use tagged or per-kind structures, not a flat optional envelope. |
+| Event, recovery, and public-wire proof is not closed-world. | Inventory every current `session.*` event plus session request/result events. Each row must prove committed fact, emission owner, canonical identity fields, payload adequacy, public visibility, criticality, durable scan owner, idempotency key, duplicate/stale behavior, and proof selector. `events.NoPayload` is allowed only when the row proves envelope fields are sufficient. |
+| Runtime/reconciler boundaries, diagnostics, and budgets are not materialized. | `BOUNDARY_MATRIX.yaml`, `DIAGNOSTICS_MANIFEST.yaml`, operation-specific `RuntimeIntent` rows, pure-decider import/call guards, runtime-missing anti-flap rows, large-city performance evidence, and production `bdstore` subprocess accounting are mandatory before behavior-moving slices that consume them. |
+| Attempt artifact paths are inconsistent. | Unfixable in this document: persona synthesis source beads for attempt 16 still stamped paths under `attempt-1`. The workflow formula owns that path calculation. This design consumes `.gc/design-reviews/ga-unpr2y/attempt-16/synthesis.md` as the authoritative attempt 16 synthesis. |
+
